  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.1\nOn this page\nLevel: beginner\nRecords in a mobile app list consist of the following data blocks: title, subtitle, and additional columns (Fig. 1).\nThe title can display only one column out of the box. All the other blocks can display any data as per your settings.\nYou can display a maximum of 13 lookup columns in a list. Columns of other types have no restrictions.\nFig. 1 Columns of the Contacts section list in the mobile application\n![Fig.\u00a01 Columns of the Contacts section list in the mobile application](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/NoCode_Customization/mobile_list_setup/scr_record_components_0.png)\n## Set up the list\u200b\n1. Click ![btn_system_designer.png](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/NoCode_Customization/mobile_list_setup/btn_system_designer.png) to **open the System Designer**.\n2. Go to the **System setup** block \u2192 **Mobile application wizard**.\n3. **Select the needed section** \u2192 **List setup** (Fig. 2).\nFig. 2 Set up a section list\n![Fig.\u00a02 Set up a section list](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/NoCode_Customization/mobile_list_setup/scr_mobile_application_wizard.png)\n4. **Click** **New column** and select a column from the list. You can drag columns to change their positions.\nFig. 3 Add columns to a section list\n![Fig.\u00a03 Add columns to a section list](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/NoCode_Customization/mobile_list_setup/scr_section_list.png)\n5. **Save the changes**.\nAs a result, Creatio will display new data in the section list (Fig. 4).\nFig. 4 Customized list of contacts in the Creatio mobile app\n![Fig.\u00a04 Customized list of contacts in the Creatio mobile app](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/NoCode_Customization/mobile_list_setup/scr_customized_list.png)\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Set up mobile app workplaces](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1391)\n[Set up mobile application section page](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1394)\n[Set up mobile application detail](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1395)",
